reviews.review_msg: Lots of reading and assignments based off the reading. But at least it's online articles and he chose an affordable text. Interesting material, clearly his passion, too much focus on defining the field/its reception for my taste. Fair and quick grader, good feedback, class discussions so do your homework every week to get a good grade.

Lectures are a bit disorganized and off topic but fascinating all the same. I can understand why some would consider her to be a bad prof for 131: that subject is not her 'baby': it's a 100 level course she HAS to teach. She rocks in 344 and 333, her preferred subjects. Wide breadth of knowledge.
